UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Shopping from Home.

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: James May's Things You Need To Know About Science
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Evolution: James May treks off to find out how Charles Darwin's theory of natural selection explains why we are all mutants and what war is actually good for. S2 Ep3

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: James May's Things You Need To Know About Science
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Speed: James explains all we need to know about speed - including how to dodge a hurricane - with a fast-moving mix of animation and motion graphics. S2 Ep4

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Rick Stein's Road to Mexico

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Bangers & Cash

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Cortina 2000E/Daimler V250: Nothing screams 1970s more than a Mk3 Ford Cortina 2000E. Derek Mathewson heads to Brigg to value a 1974 example with classic Coke bottle styling and a Pinto engine. S4 Ep4

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Richard Osman's House of Games

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Richard Osman's House of Games

Film4.uk.title: Jason and the Argonauts

Film4.uk.title: Gemini Man

Film4.uk.title: Daredevil
Film4.uk.description: (2003) Superhero fantasy. Ben Affleck is a blind lawyer who turns vigilante by night. Jennifer Garner plays his lover and Colin Farrell the villain who endangers them both. Strong violence.

Film4.uk.title: Ghost Rider

Film4.uk.title: Riders of Justice
Film4.uk.description: (2020) Darkly comic thriller with Mads Mikkelsen. A soldier recruits three geeks to help him hunt down his wife's killer. In Danish/subs.

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Cornwall with Simon Reeve
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Simon Reeve investigates the environmental challenges facing Cornwall and the rest of the country and also encounters some of the county's iconic wildlife. S1 Ep2

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Ford Escort Mexico: Derek has sold everything from trucks to bicycles - but he can't remember the last time he auctioned off a two-seater plane. S7 Ep3

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Sunbeam Rapier: 100 motorbikes come in for auction from every era of the 20th century. Also, the team assess a 1965 Vanden Plas Princess with a four litre Rolls Royce engine. S7 Ep4

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Abandoned Engineering
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Defenders Of Liberty: A now silent site that played a pivotal role defending the U.S through the 20th century. Plus, a crumbling Italian fortress and a ghostly Ukrainian mansion. S6 Ep6

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Abandoned Engineering
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Space Plane: A juggernaut of Soviet engineering which was crucial to the international space race. Deserted Scottish coastal defences and a complex that's crucial to American history. S6 Ep7

UAndYesterday.uk.title: World War Weird
UAndYesterday.uk.description: The Germans hear that Polish forces are fighting alongside a huge bear. Tales of this beer-swilling, chain-smoking beast terrify them - but incredibly the stories are true. S2 Ep8

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Teleshopping
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Shopping from Home.

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Great Continental Railway Journeys
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Lyon to Marseille: Michael Portillo travels through France from Lyon down to Marseille on the Mediterranean coast, where he joins a pilot boat leading a supertanker to its berth. S3 Ep6

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Great Continental Railway Journeys
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Sofia to Istanbul: Armed with his 1913 Bradshaw's Continental Railway Guide, Michael Portillo travels from Sofia to Istanbul along part of the route taken by the Orient Express. S4 Ep1

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Datsun 240Z/Rover Mini Cooper: Derek picks up some emerging sporting classics from the far east when three Datsun Zs appear, and an unusual lot arrives that run on caterpillar tracks not wheels. S3 Ep

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Fiat X1/9 / Austin A60 Cambridge: There's real Yorkshire drama when Derek sells vehicles from TV show Heartbeat, love for an Austin Cambridge, and a sporty Italian number getting rehomed. S3 Ep6

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Auschwitz: The Nazis and the Final Solution
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Orders and Initiatives: Charting the evolution of Auschwitz. This episode looks at the development of the 'Final Solution'. S1 Ep2

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Secret Nazi Bases
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Into the Wolf's Den: Allied forces stumble across a sprawling complex in the French countryside. What did the Nazis have planned for this mysterious Nazi stronghold? S3 Ep1

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Antiques Roadshow
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Clissold Park 1: Fiona Bruce presents the show from Clissold Park in the London Borough of Hackney, where treasures include some pricey whisky bottles. S45 Ep4

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Antiques Roadshow
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Brodie Castle and Estate, Morayshire 2: Fiona Bruce presents the show from the grounds of Brodie Castle in Scotland, where treasures include football memorabilia. S45 Ep5

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Fiat 500: A rusty 1970 Fiat 500 goes under the hammer - Derek reckons it's the kind of vehicle that is so iconic that it has to be saved. S7 Ep5

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Willys Jeep: Tucked away in the showroom is a WW2-era Willys Jeep. Its original condition means there might be a bunfight for a military vehicle that's ripe for restoration. S7 Ep6

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Great Canal Journeys
UAndYesterday.uk.description: The Norfolk Broads: Tim and Pru explore one of Britain's most ancient and picturesque waterways to discover the area's unique way of life, ruins, fens, marshes and woodlands. S5 Ep3

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Flipping Bangers
UAndYesterday.uk.description: New. Audi TT: Gus and Will find an Audi Quattro roadster than has seen better days - it's full of problems, and hasn't been serviced in years. Even so, they are intent on renovating it. S2 Ep13

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash: Restoring Classics
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Project X / Beach Cruiser: The team buy one of Derek's favourite Austin commercials and convert it to electric, and also snap up a super-rare 50's American beach bike. S6 Ep1

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Fiat 500: A rusty 1970 Fiat 500 goes under the hammer - Derek reckons it's the kind of vehicle that is so iconic that it has to be saved. S7 Ep5

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Willys Jeep: Tucked away in the showroom is a WW2-era Willys Jeep. Its original condition means there might be a bunfight for a military vehicle that's ripe for restoration. S7 Ep6

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Manta/Berlinetta/TR7/BSA Bike: Dave travels to Bedale to extract a barn find - a 1984 Manta GTE which hasn't seen the light of day in thirty years. S9 Ep13

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: VW Golf Cabriolet: Derek and Paul are off to Leeds on a rare father and son road trip to pick up a VW Cabriolet and a Lotus Elite. S8 Ep1

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Jaguar Challenger XJ6: A beautiful looking sports car has been fooling the punters and intriguing Derek. It's a Challenger E-Type - a fibreglass replica created from an E-Type mould. S8 Ep2

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: 1961 Morris Minor 1000: Paul and Jack head to Staffordshire to pick up five vehicles from collector Rob's colossal barn, including a Mini and a Morris Minor. S8 Ep3

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: 'Allo 'Allo!
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: An Enigma Variation: Mercifully politically incorrect comedy. All is chaos as Rene attempts to hide the stolen gold. Meanwhile the Resistance plan to steal the Enigma Encoder. S5 Ep23

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: 'Allo 'Allo!
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Renewing the Vows: More abuse of the French language. Rene is shocked when Edith accepts Alfonse's proposal. Will he lose the cafe and the gold bars he lifted? S5 Ep24

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: 'Allo 'Allo!
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: The Big Flush: Laughs at the expense of the French, Germans, English and anyone else. Rene decides it's time he quit his dangerous lifestyle - along with the four gold bars. S5 Ep25

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: 'Allo 'Allo!
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Who's for the Vatican?: No stone unturned in the quest to send up every nation in the EU. A medal, a suicide pill and a hide-out in the Vatican introduce an old habit to Rene. S5 Ep12

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Teleshopping
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Shopping from Home.

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Great Continental Railway Journeys
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Rome to Taormina: Michael Portillo travels down the spine of Italy from Rome to Sicily, along the way visiting Naples to find out about the country's first railway. S3 Ep2

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Great Continental Railway Journeys
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Warsaw to Krakow: Michael Portillo uses his 1913 copy of Bradshaw's Continental Railway Guide to explore Poland, visiting Warsaw, Lodz, Poznan, Wroclaw and Krakow along the way. S3 Ep3

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Adolf Hitler's War
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Vernichtungskrieg: Adolf Hitler has his mind on making Germany into a great empire by expanding eastwards, but his invasion of Poland tips the world into a violent and bloody war. S1 Ep1

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Adolf Hitler's War
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: A Superhuman Act of Inhumanity: Betrayed, Stalin fights the German army in the Soviet states. The German occupation policies lead to the first extermination policies of 'undesirables'. S1 Ep2

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Adolf Hitler's War
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Moscow Is Behind Us: As Hitler's troops advance, occupants in Ukraine, Belarus and Poland take the brunt of the occupying forces cruelty; and the first concentration camps are created. S1 Ep3

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Canal Boat Diaries
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Braunston to Lapworth: Robbie Cumming journeys through Royal Leamington Spa and the historic town of Warwick with its medieval castle. S5 Ep1

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Canal Boat Diaries
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Yardley Wood to Netherton Tunnel: Robbie Cumming sets out to explore the meandering waterways of inner city Birmingham including the Soho Loop and the Engine Arm Canal. S5 Ep2

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Canal Boat Diaries
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Hawne Basin to Stourbridge: Disaster strikes when the Naughty Lass collides with a low bridge on the Bumble Hole Canal Branch damaging a chimney. S5 Ep3

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Motorhoming with Merton and Webster
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: New. Paul and Suki head for Somerset on the next leg of their grand UK tour in their motorhome that has now officially christened as Captain Narrow Squeak. S1 Ep3

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Motorhoming with Merton and Webster
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: New. Paul and Suki venture into Wales and the Bannau Brycheiniog - Brecon Beacons - National Park for this instalment of their UK motorhoming adventure. S1 Ep4

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Operation Amsterdam
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Second World War adventure. A British Army officer sets out to thwart the Nazis by stealing a secret cache of diamonds from a bank in Amsterdam.

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Incredible Journeys with Simon Reeve
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: A look at the challenge of preserving unspoilt wildernesses, from the icy expanses of Siberia to the tropical forests of central and South America. S1 Ep4

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Robson Green's Weekend Escapes
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Former footballer Les Ferdinand is coerced into the North Sea in a wetsuit as he joins Robson Green on a short break in Northumberland packed with memories and laughter. S1 Ep1

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Robson Green's Weekend Escapes
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Robson and actor Mark Benton go on a humour-filled quest to find ways to relax while exploring the North Yorkshire coast. S1 Ep2

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Flipping Bangers
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Citroen XM: Gus has his eye on a Citroen XM that looks amazing - but it's in France. Will isn't sure, but the engineering challenges win him over. S2 Ep12

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: 1924 Rover 9HP Tourer: Paul collects a cherished 1924 Rover 9 that's been in the same family since the 1950s and only had one previous owner before that. S8 Ep6

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: 1954 Morgan Plus 4 Coupe: Derek heads north to pick up a 1954 Morgan Plus 4 coupe in mint condition and believed to be just one of three still on the road. S8 Ep7

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: 1968 Ford Cortina: Derek waxes lyrical about a pristine Jaguar XJ8 and a Ford Model T van tests his driving skills. S8 Ep8

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Ford Cortina/GT Savage Estate: Derek travels to the Yorkshire coast to pick up a 1963 Austin J2 Paralanian campervan described as the Rolls Royce of campervans. S9 Ep1

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Capri/Alpine/Lancia Fulvia Zagato: Derek heads to Sunderland to pick up a real Italian beauty - a 1972 Lancia Fulvia Zagato. Red and racy, the car has seen better days but Derek's still impressed. S9

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Teleshopping
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Shopping from Home.

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Great Continental Railway Journeys
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: La Coruna to Lisbon: Michael Portillo travels through Spain and Portugal, meeting people from all over the world on the pilgrims' trail to Santiago de Compostela in Galicia. S3 Ep4

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Great Continental Railway Journeys
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Haifa to the Negev: Michael Portillo travels through Israel and Palestine, visiting Jerusalem's Christian, Jewish and Muslim quarters and Bethlehem in the West Bank. S3 Ep5

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Armstrong Siddeley/Triumph Herald: Derek takes a shine to a rare 1958 Armstrong Siddeley Sapphire with a long family history and a convertible Triumph Herald brings a few smiles on auction day. S3 Ep3

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: DB6/Merc Unimog Fire Engine: An Aston Martin DB6 in need of total restoration looks set to break the Mathewsons auction record and news of a rare Vincent motorbike arriving causes a stir. S3 Ep4

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Surprising Beginnings: Charting the evolution of Auschwitz concentration camp and the mentality of its perpetrators. This episode looks at the camp's beginnings. S1 Ep1

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Brodie Castle & Estate, Morayshire 1: At Brodie Castle in Morayshire Fiona Bruce meets a Highland Games commentator who has brought a brooch presented by Queen Victoria. S45 Ep3
